HEADWORD: Britisher
<hw>Brit"ish*er</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An Englishman; a subject or
inhabitant of Great Britain, esp. one in the British military or naval
service.</def> <mark>[Now used jocosely]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

